---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — SiteSync"
  description="SiteSync is building construction project management that respects how the work actually flows."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-prose px-6 pt-24 pb-12 text-brand-ink">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold">About SiteSync</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-brand-mute">
      Construction software is mostly built for accounting and procurement.
      The Field — the people actually putting work in place — get a desktop
      tool ported to mobile and called good enough.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-brand-mute">
      SiteSync is built around the workflow the field actually uses: take a
      photo, ask a question, log the day, route a submittal, close a punch
      item. The AI Copilot drafts the paperwork; you approve. The audit chain
      proves what happened, when, and to whom.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-brand-mute">
      We're a small team in Dallas. Email
      <a href="mailto:walker@sitesyncai.com" class="text-brand-accent hover:underline">
        walker@sitesyncai.com
      </a>
      to talk.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
